en: Widespread storm system to sweep South Australia, Victoria, and NSW as heatwave and extreme fire danger persist, extending into Tasmania and southern Queensland. South-east Australia braces for a severe weather onslaught, with thunderstorms, large hail, and damaging winds set to strike alongside extreme heat. la: Systema tempestatis divulgatum Australium Australiam, Victoriam, et NSW evertendi ut periculum caloris et ignis extremi perseuerent, in Tasmania et Queenslandia australi extenduntur. Australis-orientalis Australia gravibus tempestatum incursibus adstringit, cum procellis, grandinibus, et ventis damnosis ad extremum caloris e regione percutiendum.
